**[1846, 05-28] Ms.B.1.6.3.12**

Haughton to May Jr.

Various subjects, including Free Church and Oregon situation. Liked
letters of May’s that appeared in the *Inquirer*. **BAA 205.** He is an
Irish Repealer but doesn’t “take active part in the movement, for I have
little faith in the value of merely political agitation.”


